03:49','CollectorCollection'),(150,NULL,22,'Metal Figures','metal-figures','<p>H.S. Brumms flat metal</p>\n\n<p>$400 sold</p>\n',5,578,0,0,0,1,0,1,1,NULL,'2009-04-13 23:30:45','2012-02-10 13:02:57','CollectorCollection'),(151,NULL,66,'Dinosaur and Other Animal Models','dinosaur-and-other-animal-models','<p>Various Dinosaur and animal Models</p>\n',15,1190,1,0,0,1,0,1,1,NULL,'2009-06-14 21:12:58','2012-02-10 13:02:57','CollectorCollection'),(152,NULL,683,'Vintage Rubber Toys','vintage-rubber-toys','<p>Vintage and retro plastic, rubber &amp;/or squeaky toys.</p>\n',8,3704,13,0,0,1,0,1,1,NULL,'2009-09-02 03:26:43','2012-02-10 13:02:57','CollectorCollection'),(153,NULL,329,'The Museum UnCut Funk Movie Poster  Collection','the-museum-uncut-funk-movie-poster-collection','<p>The collection includes a small sample of Italian movie posters from the 1970\'s Blaxploitation film genre. To view the entire collection of The Museum of Uncut Funk please visit www.museumofuncutfunk.com</p>\n',10,1279,0,0,0,1,0,1,1,NULL,'2009-05-03 19:28:40','2012-02-10 13:02:57','CollectorCollection'),(154,NULL,116,'Black Animation','black-animation','<p>The Museum of UnCut Funk Collection includes original production drawings and cels and limited edition cels from the 1970’s,1980’s and 1990’s. Please visit The Museum of UnCut Funk to see more of our collection of Black animation and read our animation blogs.</p>\n',3,927,1,0,0,1,0,1,1,NULL,'2009-05-04 20:07:13','2012-02-10 13:02:57','CollectorCollection'),(155,NULL,250,'Black Comic Books and Graphic Novels','black-comic-books-and-graphic-novels','<p>The Museum of UnCut Funk Collection includes Luke Cage, Storm and other comic books from the 1960‘s, 1970’s and early 1980’s. Please visit to see more of our collection at The Museum of UnCut Funk. www.museumofuncutfunk.com</p>\n',3,865,1,0,0,1,0,1,1,NULL,'2009-05-04 20:24:47','2012-02-10 13:02:57','CollectorCollection'),(156,NULL,53,'Blacks on Stamps ','blacks-on-stamps','<p>The Museum of UnCut Funk Collection includes The Black Heritage Series from the USPS and other stamps featuring Blacks on them. Please visit The Museum of UnCut Funk to read our stamp collecting blog.</p>\n',1,523,0,0,0,1,0,1,1,NULL,'2009-05-04 20:59:35','2012-02-10 13:02:57','CollectorCollection'),(157,NULL,16,'Blacks on Currency and Gold Medals','blacks-on-currency-and-gold-medals','<p>The Museum of UnCut Funk Collection includes a collection of gold coin and medal featuring Blacks. Please visit The Museum of UnCut Funk at www.museumofuncutfunk.com to read our blogs about our collection. </p>\n',3,782,0,0,0,1,0,1,1,NULL,'2009-05-04 20:46:56','2012-02-10 13:02:57','CollectorCollection'),(158,NULL,675,'Playmobil : April 2009 ','playmobil-april-2009','<p>I adore Playmobil - simple and strange. Here\'s a photo gallery of some of their April 2009 releases, from Nautical Expeditions, Police and Wedding.</p>\n',86,1957,4,0,0,1,0,1,1,NULL,'2009-05-19 23:40:35','2012-02-10 13:02:57','CollectorCollection'),(159,NULL,2,'Dino King and Happinet Dinosaurs','dino-king-and-happinet-dinosaurs','<p>dino king and happinet dinosaurs</p>\n',3,2184,0,0,0,1,0,1,1,NULL,'2009-05-17 23:04:18','2012-02-10 13:02:57','CollectorCollection'),(160,NULL,2,'Older collection pics','older-collection-pics','<p>pictured of collection 2 yrs ago.</p>\n',9,868,0,0,0,1,0,1,1,NULL,'2009-05-17 23:45:07','2012-02-10 13:02:57','CollectorCollection'),(161,NULL,3,'Blacks on Crate Labels','blacks-on-crate-labels','<p>I collect crate labels from the pre-civil rights era. While these labels are racist and offensive, I appreciate them for their artwork. I also believe that they are important historical artifacts to preserve as a reminder that this type of product labeling should never be tolerated again.</p>\n\n<p>Below is a small sampling of the Original Black Crate Labels that are a part of The Museum of UnCut Funk Collection.</p>\n',6,751,0,0,0,1,0,1,1,NULL,'2009-05-24 23:45:06','2012-02-10 13:02:57','CollectorCollection'),(162,NULL,17,'Golden Legacy Series of Black History Comic Books','golden-legacy-series-of-black-history-comic-books','<p>Bertram A Fitzgerald is the publisher of the Golden Legacy Series of Black History Comic Books. During the decade between 1966 and 1976 he acted as editor and publisher for the series and wrote almost half the books. To read more about the series please visit The Museum of UnCut Funk blog Can\'t Get Enough...Og That Funky Stuff at www.museumofuncutfunk.com</p>\n',16,2193,1,0,0,1,0,1,1,NULL,'2009-05-29 00:08:26','2012-02-10 13:02:57','CollectorCollection'),(163,NULL,3,'Black Fashion Ads','black-fashion-ads','<p>From the archives of The Museum of UnCut Funk Flagg Brothers Couture. For a trip down memory lane in funky mens fashion please visit www.museumofuncutfunk.com and read our Can\'t Get Enough of That Funky Stuff blog.</p>\n',7,2896,13,0,0,1,0,1,1,NULL,'2009-05-30 11:07:21','2012-02-10 13:02:57','CollectorCollection'),(164,NULL,3,'Broadway in Black','broadway-in-black','<p>Please visit www.museumofuncutfunk.com and read our Can\'t Get Enough of That Funky Stuff blog on Broadway in Black.</p>\n',5,886,0,0,0,1,0,1,1,NULL,'2009-05-31 17:06:15','2012-02-10 13:02:57','CollectorCollection'),(165,NULL,2,'Mr. Bean 1/6th Figure','mr-bean-1-6th-figure','<p>Mr. Bean from Enterbay is the most unexpected figure I\'ve ever seen. So, of course, I had to get one.</p>\n',17,2364,0,0,0,1,0,1,1,NULL,'2009-06-12 22:13:24','2012-02-10 13:02:57','CollectorCollection'),(166,NULL,3,'Vintage Rhum Labels','vintage-rhum-labels','<p>The Museum of UnCut Funk has a small collection of vintage rum labels. The Curators favorite labels are the old French Rhum labels from the early nineteen hundreds. These often have Black people of West Indian or African descent, usually accompanied by poorly spelt English words translated from French.</p>\n\n<p>To see more of the Curators collection please visit The Museum of UnCut Funk at www.museumofuncutfunk.com</p>\n',5,1078,0,0,0,1,0,1,1,NULL,'2009-06-14 14:29:32','2012-02-10 13:02:57','CollectorCollection'),(167,NULL,769,'My Wild Animals','my-wild-animals','<p>My wildlife collection!(not ubdated)</p>\n',17,2735,3,0,0,1,0,1,1,NULL,'2009-07-14 14:31:51','2012-02-10 13:02:57','CollectorCollection'),(168,NULL,769,'Farm Life','farm-life','<p>Waited too much for other collections?Here they are:farm animals!</p>\n',10,1173,0,0,0,1,0,1,1,NULL,'2009-07-14 13:16:36','2012-02-10 13:02:57','CollectorCollection'),(169,NULL,22,'Animal dioramas','animal-dioramas','<p>Photos of my figurines living in natural enverioments outside the house and between the walls.</p>\n',8,1520,3,0,0,1,0,1,1,NULL,'2010-02-09 10:53:54','2012-02-10 13:02:57','CollectorCollection'),(170,NULL,250,'Jurassic Park Comic Books','jurassic-park-comic-books','<p>Most of these Jurassic Park Comic Books were purchased in a binder from the estate of a comic book collector/dealer.</p>\n',22,4438,0,0,0,1,0,1,1,NULL,'2009-06-19 12:42:56','2012-02-10 13:02:57','CollectorCollection'),(171,NULL,675,'Artoyz Elements : Unboxing','artoyz-elements-unboxing','<p>Artoyz Elements series was first released exclusively in France, and only recently has come to the US. It\'s a beautiful little series based on the idea of the four elements. Here\'s the unboxing process.</p>\n',9,696,0,0,0,1,0,1,1,NULL,'2009-06-20 00:32:58','2012-02-10 13:02:57','CollectorCollection'),(172,NULL,250,'Spoof Comics Presents Soul Trek','spoof-comics-presents-soul-trek','<p>Spoof Comics presents SoulTrek, a combination of Soul Train and Star Trek. Say What??? Okay, maybe not the best comic, but what a brilliant idea for Spoof comic book fans. </p>\n\n<p>Please visit The Museum of UnCut Funk and read our Can\'t Get Enough of That Funky Stuff Blog for more of Spoof Comics.\nwww.funkystuffblog.com</p>\n\n<p>Please visit The Museum of UnCut Funk and read our Can\'t Get Enough of That Funky Stuff Blog for more of Spoof Comics.\nwww.funkystuffblog.com</p>\n',2,730,0,0,0,1,0,1,1,NULL,'2009-06-22 18:16:18','2012-02-10 13:02:57','CollectorCollection'),(173,NULL,17,'GunHawks Vol 1 -7','gunhawks-vol-1-7','<p>The Gunhawks were Kid Cassidy and Reno Jones. As introduced in Gunhawks #1 (1972), Cassidy was the son of a plantation-owning family in the antebellum American South, and Jones was a Black employee of the family who was friends with Cassidy.</p>\n\n<p>Please visit The Museum of UnCut Funk and read our Can\'t Get Enough of That Funky Stuff Blog to see our western comic book collection and read more about racism in the old west. www.funkystuffblog.com</p>\n',7,694,0,0,0,1,0,1,1,NULL,'2009-06-22 18:10:16','2012-02-10 13:02:57','CollectorCollection'),(174,NULL,766,'A Comic Tribute to Michael Jackson ','a-comic-tribute-to-michael-jackson','<p>The Museum of UnCut Funk is working through profound sadness over the passing of Michael Jackson. We honor him in this blog with a quick look at his career as a comic book character from the collection of the Curator.</p>\n\n<p>Please visit The Museum of UnCut Funk to read more on our Comic Tribute to Michael Jackson. www.koolcatshipchicksblog.com.</p>\n',12,1155,2,0,0,1,0,1,1,NULL,'2009-07-23 21:45:53','2012-02-10 13:02:57','CollectorCollection'),(175,NULL,102,'June 27 2009 Garage Sale Finds','june-27-2009-garage-sale-finds','<p>You know its going to be a good garage sale weekend when there\'s an ad in the paper advertising \"lots of dinosaur toys\"</p>\n',29,1851,2,0,0,1,0,1,1,NULL,'2009-07-03 11:47:06','2012-02-10 13:02:57','CollectorCollection'),(176,NULL,752,'SDCC Mez-Itz Show Preview','sdcc-mez-itz-show-preview','<p>Mezco was kind enough to drop some picture love on us for a preview of the upcoming Mez-Itz inaugural show at San Diego Comic Con this summer. Enjoy!</p>\n',20,1363,0,0,0,1,0,1,1,NULL,'2009-07-10 21:22:42','2012-02-10 13:02:57','CollectorCollection'),(177,NULL,116,'Jackson Five Animation','jackson-five-animation','<p>The Museum of UnCut Funk Collection includes original production drawings and cels and limited edition cels from the 1970’s,1980’s and 1990’s. The Curator\'s collection includes original production cels from The Jackson Five cartoon series. </p>\n',5,1768,1,0,0,1,0,1,1,NULL,'2009-07-11 18:34:26','2012-02-10 13:02:57','CollectorCollection'),(178,NULL,329,'The X Files','the-x-files','<p>Memorabilia of the 90\'s series tv The X Files sales overworld, signs, rare items, limited items, spanish and english editions, etc.</p>\n',3,639,0,0,0,1,0,1,1,NULL,'2009-07-15 07:56:48','2012-02-10 13:02:57','CollectorCollection'),(179,NULL,22,'Unknown maker animals!!!','unknown-maker-animals','<p>You know my profile?No...?!Then let me remind you than when I was 2 years old I had some animal toys by unknown makers.By 5,I had 500 of them.At six,I started collecting hand-painted animals.Now I only have 200 China toys.Imagine how it was with 500 after you see my collection ;) Have fun!</p>\n',18,2227,0,0,0,1,0,1,1,NULL,'2010-02-27 15:43:58','2012-02-10 13:02:57','CollectorCollection'),(180,NULL,24,'UnCut Funk Board Games','uncut-funk-board-games','<p>The Museum of UnCut Funk has a unique collection of 1970\'s and 80\'s  board games featuring Black characters such as the Harlem Globetrotters, The Jackson Five, Fat Albert and The A-Team. Please visit Can\'t Get Enough of That Funky Stuff blog to read more. www.funkystuffblog.com</p>\n',3,887,1,0,0,1,0,1,1,NULL,'2009-07-23 22:34:33','2012-02-10 13:02:57','CollectorCollection'),(181,NULL,22,'Small dinosaur and prehistoric animal figures','small-dinosaur-and-prehistoric-animal-figures','<p>small shelf full of mainly kaiyodos</p>\n',11,1243,2,0,0,1,0,1,1,NULL,'2009-07-31 14:10:41','2012-02-10 13:02:57','CollectorCollection'),(182,NULL,9,'Children\'s Activities Books','childrens-activities-books','<p>Retro &amp; vintage books &amp; booklets for kids, including coloring books, sticker books, scratch &amp; sniff, mazes etc.</p>\n',4,648,0,0,0,1,0,1,1,NULL,'2009-08-25 22:54:30','2012-02-10 13:02:57','CollectorCollection'),(183,NULL,250,'Crazy Magazine ','crazy-magazine','<p>For a short time in the early 1970\'s, Crazy magazine, a competitor of Mad and Cracked magazines was published by Marvel Comics. During this period Crazy magazine payed tribute to many Black celebrities in the area of film, music and television.\nPlease visit The Museum of UnCut Funk blog Can\'t Get Enough of That Funky Stuff blog to read more. www.funkystuffblog.com.</p>\n',2,649,0,0,0,1,0,1,1,NULL,'2009-08-22 11:17:46','2012-02-10 13:02:57','CollectorCollection'),(184,NULL,250,'Lois Lane #106','lois-lane-106','<p>?I am Curious (Black)” the first story in Superman’s Girlfriend Lois Lane #106. The Museum of UnCut Funk has acquired this comic book to our comic book collection. Please visit the Can\'t Get Enough of that Stuff blog to read more. www.funkystuffblog.com</p>\n',2,830,0,0,0,1,0,1,1,NULL,'2009-08-22 11:45:33','2012-02-10 13:02:57','CollectorCollection'),(185,NULL,752,'Futurama Minis from Kid Robot','futurama-minis-from-kid-robot','<p>A collection of mini vinyl figured depicting the Futurama universe, made by Kid Robot.</p>\n',14,1249,2,0,0,1,0,1,1,NULL,'2009-08-22 21:00:33','2012-02-10 13:02:57','CollectorCollection'),(186,NULL,9,'Vintage Hardcover Books','vintage-hardcover-books','<p>Assorted vintage, antique &amp; retro hardcover books.</p>\n',4,1237,1,0,0,1,0,1,1,NULL,'2009-09-02 06:53:02','2012-02-10 13:02:57','CollectorCollection'),(187,NULL,611,'Vintage &amp; Retro Sewing Patterns','vintage-amp-retro-sewing-patterns','<p>Assorted sewing patterns</p>\n',3,949,0,0,0,1,0,1,1,NULL,'2009-08-25 18:07:50','2012-02-10 13:02:57','CollectorCollection'),(188,NULL,20,'Dolls &amp; Doll Accessories','dolls-amp-doll-accessories','<p>Vintage, antique &amp; retro dolls, doll boxes, clothing &amp; accessories for dolls.</p>\n',8,1122,0,0,0,1,0,1,1,NULL,'2009-08-25 22:07:02','2012-02-10 13:02:57','CollectorCollection'),(189,NULL,116,'The Censored Eleven at The Museum of UnCut Funk','the-censored-eleven-at-the-museum-of-uncut-funk','<p>The Mus